column2: There's no I in Teamocil. At least not where you think. Teamocil is a simple tool used to automatically create windows and panes in tmux with YAML files.

column5:
Merge pull request #129 from jli1972/home-directory-fix

added support for home directory which contains white space(s)
added support for home directory which contains white space(s)

Merge pull request #123 from electrocucaracha/master

Default value for $EDITOR

Add default editor

If the EDITOR environment variable is not defined it's raised a
Permission denied error, which is not associated with the file
that the user pretends to edit. This change provides *vi* as default
editor.
Add custom window layout section back in README.md
